=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Tutorials_05-Functions-and-Sound_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: moderate
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -13.6282
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5000
  pitch_clarity: 241.7273
  inharmonicity: 0.0010
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -4.2091
  resonance_freq: 430.6641

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: 05. Functions and Sound Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Tutorials/Getting-Started/05-Functions-and-Sound.html
// Tags: 05-Functions-and-Sound, Tutorials
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
(
{ var ampOsc;
    ampOsc = SinOsc.kr(0.5, 1.5pi, 0.5, 0.5);
    SinOsc.ar(440, 0, ampOsc);
}.play;
)
